

= active with participatory architecture

=Bio=

"Patrizia Di Monte architect by IUAV Venice, master in Large Scale architecture and PHD on New Architectural Tools, town planning professor at the ETSA-USJ and Ignacio Grávalos, architect by ETSA Barcelona, Architectural Graphic Expression professor at the ETSAZ-USJ, founded gravalosdimonte architects in 1998, in the city of Zaragoza. Their works are published in several Architectural and cultural rewies. They are carrying on cultural projects, covering art and architecture, urban regeneration and strategies, landscaping, participative architecture, sustainable urbanism and creativity. They are the estonoesunsolar programme masterminds."


